---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TimeLineElement from "../components/cv/TimeLine.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" sideBarActiveItemID="cv">
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">About</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-10 text-justify">
    <p class="mb-4">
      I'm Pete Baxter, a Principal Cloud Solution Architect at Microsoft. I've
      been here since 1998, and I've spent the last several years focused on
      financial services and banking, helping some of the largest regulated
      enterprises design and run secure workloads on Azure.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-4">
      My current focus is enterprise Network Architecture on Azure: Virtual WAN
      and ExpressRoute, Hub-and-Spoke Topologies, and Secure Connectivity at
      scale. Close behind are the regulated-cloud workloads I've spent years on:
      Azure Government and FedRAMP High, AKS and Container Platforms, Capacity
      and Resiliency, and the Security and Governance controls that have to hold
      up under audit. Much of that is operational work: disaster recovery,
      capacity planning, platform migrations, and finding the root cause of the
      incident at 2 a.m.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Alongside the customer work, I lead a worldwide train-the-trainer program
      for Microsoft's cloud architects and have owned new-hire and
      trainer-development content for over 15 years. I'm also deep in AI tooling
      for engineers, working hands-on with GitHub Copilot, the Copilot CLI, and
      Microsoft Scout, and serving as an early adopter and design partner for
      Microsoft's internal AI tools.
    </p>
    <p>
      Outside work, I've been married for 31 years and I'm a father of five,
      based in Charlotte, North Carolina. When I'm not in front of a terminal
      you'll find me hiking, swimming, building things in Minecraft with my kids,
      or automating some new corner of my smart home.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Experience</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Principal Cloud Solution Architect"
      subtitle="Microsoft · 2022 – Present"
    >
      Architecture lead for major financial services and banking customers on
      Azure. Current focus on enterprise connectivity (Azure Virtual WAN,
      ExpressRoute) and AI tooling for engineers, with regulated workloads
      (Azure Government / FedRAMP High), AKS resiliency and DR, capacity
      assurance, and cloud security. Frequent escalation point for
      high-severity architecture and incident work.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Senior Cloud Solution Architect"
      subtitle="Microsoft · 2016 – 2022"
    >
      Moved from on-product field engineering into Azure architecture, building
      cloud delivery skills across the Cloud Adoption and Well-Architected
      Frameworks, landing zones, and financial-services workloads.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Senior Premier Field Engineer"
      subtitle="Microsoft · 2006 – 2016"
    >
      Field engineering with a SharePoint specialty; Master Trainer and content
      owner for new-hire role-immersion training; technical lead on enterprise
      customer accounts.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Support & .NET Engineer"
      subtitle="Microsoft · 1998 – 2006"
    >
      Product support and internal-tools development in Product Support Services,
      including the Critical Situation (CritSit) management platform.
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Certifications</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc mx-6 mb-10 grid gap-2">
    <li>Microsoft Certified: Azure Solutions Architect Expert (AZ-305)</li>
    <li>Microsoft Certified: Azure Security Engineer Associate (AZ-500)</li>
    <li>Microsoft Certified: Azure Administrator Associate (AZ-104)</li>
    <li>Microsoft Certified: Azure AI Fundamentals (AI-900)</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Skills</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc md:columns-3 columns-2 mx-6">
    <li>Azure Virtual WAN</li>
    <li>Azure ExpressRoute</li>
    <li>Azure Networking &amp; Ingress</li>
    <li>Azure Architecture</li>
    <li>AKS &amp; Containers</li>
    <li>FedRAMP High / Azure Government</li>
    <li>Cloud Security &amp; Governance</li>
    <li>Resiliency &amp; Disaster Recovery</li>
    <li>Landing Zones (CAF / WAF)</li>
    <li>Infrastructure as Code</li>
    <li>Regulated / FSI Cloud</li>
    <li>GitHub Copilot &amp; Copilot CLI</li>
    <li>Microsoft Scout</li>
    <li>AI &amp; Agentic Workloads</li>
    <li>Technical Training &amp; Enablement</li>
  </ul>
</BaseLayout>
